{"serial": "43034", "department_serial": 39, "code": "IM7065", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Human Resource Management", "ch": "人力資源管理"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chou, Huey-Wen"], "ch": ["周惠文"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["5", "6", "7"]}, "loc": {"building": "I1", "room": "404"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 70, "department": {"ch": "資訊管理學系", "en": "Department of Information Management"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 2, "selected": 70, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "“This course deals with today’s human resource management for students to acquire a strong ground in all key HR functions. In today’s business environment, human capital has become one of the most important assets for any organizations. So how to compete for talent and build and deploy talent resources is one of the challenges for organization to help gaining its competitive advantage. \nAfter completing this course, you should:\n- Be able to identify each of the major HRM functions.\n- Be able to recognize the major trends, opportunities, and challenges in today’s HRM.\n- Be better able to diagnose strategic organizational situation and adopt HR techniques to address the issues.\n- Be able to equip with the fundamental competencies in HR practices as an employee in business.“", "en": "“This course deals with today’s human resource management for students to acquire a strong ground in all key HR functions. In today’s business environment, human capital has become one of the most important assets for any organizations. So how to compete for talent and build and deploy talent resources is one of the challenges for organization to help gaining its competitive advantage. \nAfter completing this course, you should:\n- Be able to identify each of the major HRM functions.\n- Be able to recognize the major trends, opportunities, and challenges in today’s HRM.\n- Be better able to diagnose strategic organizational situation and adopt HR techniques to address the issues.\n- Be able to equip with the fundamental competencies in HR practices as an employee in business.“"}, "outline": {"ch": "“課程簡介\n第一章 HRM導論\n公平雇用法令\n第三章 HRM策略與績效\n第四章 工作分析與人才管理流程\n第五章 人力規劃與招募\n第六章 測驗與甄選\n第七章 面談\n演講\n期中考\n第八章 教育訓練\n第九章 績效管理與評估\n第十章 職涯管理與留才\n第十七章 全球HRM\n第十一章 建立策略薪酬計畫\n第十二章 績效酬賞與福利\n期末考“", "en": "“Introduction\nCh. 1 Introduction to HRM\nEqual opportunity and the law\nCh. 3 Human resource management strategy and performance\nCh. 4 Job analysis and talent management process\nCh. 5 Personnel planning ＆ recruiting\nCh. 6 Employee testing and selection\nCh. 7 Interviewing candidates\nInvited speech\nMidterm examination\nCh. 8 Training and developing employees\nCh. 9 Performance management and appraisal\nCh. 10 Managing careers and retention\nCh. 17 Managing global HRM\nCh. 11 Establishing strategic pay plans\nCh. 12 Pay for performance and benefits\nFinal exam“"}, "textbook": {"ch": "“Dessler, G. Human Resource Management, 16th Edition?2020 Pearson“", "en": "“Dessler, G. Human Resource Management, 16th Edition?2020 Pearson“"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "30", "en": "30"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "“出席 10％\n課堂參與、作業 30％ \n期中考 30％\n期末考或報告 30％“", "en": "Attendance 10％\nparticpation, assignment 30％\nmidterm examination 30％\nfinal examination 30％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "個別約定", "en": "by appointment"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "安排學生自主學習以上課中發表討論。", "en": "Arrange time slot for independent study and in class discussion"}, "domain": {"ch": "商管知識", "en": "商管知識"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "原創性", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "熟悉其專業領域文獻", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書